    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka extends multiple-entry tourist visa to five years",
      "author": "Mahadiya Hamza",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has extended its multiple-entry tourist visa up to five years to boost repeat tourism, Minister of Tourism Harin Fernando said.",
        "The island currently offers one-year multiple entry visas and single entry visas with a sixth-month stay period.",
        "\u201cCabinet has approved a 5-year multiple entry tourist visas 6-months stay for 35 countries to help boost repeat tourism in Sri Lanka (sp),\u201d Fernando tweeted on Tuesday August 30.",
        "In addition to the 1 yr multiple entry & single entry tourists visas which have 6 months stay period (previously 30 days) cabinet has approved a 5 yr multiple entry tourist visa w/ 6 months stay for 35 countries. To help boost repeat tourism in SL. #visitsrilanka #SriLankaCan",
        "Sri Lanka earlier offered a digital nomad visa for tourists for up three months targetting travellers who worked long-distance.",
        "Initially, the 30-day visa was priced at 35 dollars for most countries and 20 dollars for SAARC nations.",
        "Sri Lanka to give digital nomad visas up to 270 days, US$500 fine for overstaying"
      ],
